  "title": "PLANNING CONSTRUCTION ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To be involved in the development and control of Project Work Schedule</li>\n  <li>Drawing up plans and presenting schedules of work, often with visual aids such as bar charts and procedures diagrams</li>\n  <li>To calculate/estimate the duration of each significant construction activity and the resource requirements</li>\n  <li>To prepare technical and drawing submissions, etc.</li>\n  <li>To be involved in site planning, work schedule and monitoring site implementation progress</li>\n  <li>Progress update against baseline throughout the construction process</li>\n  <li>Involve in coordination between sub-contractors/vendors/departments and anticipate labour/material/ equipment demands to meet schedules</li>\n  <li>Producing monthly progress reports and support in progress claims</li>\n  <li>Adherence to safety practices in the work place.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering/Construction Management and/or Equivalent</li>\n  <li>Minimum of 3 years of related working experience in the Construction industry</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Project and Primavera is a must</li>\n  <li>Experience in Construction Planning with building-related facility</li>\n  <li>Mon to Sat (Work Site - Jurong Island)</li>\n  <li>Ability to work beyond normal working hours</li>\n</ul>",
